Package com.quantcomponents.algo

Interface Summary
ICommissionCalculator Commission calculator for simulated trading and backtesting
IExecutionService Low-level interface to be implemented by broker adapters, to execute trades and gather order, trade and position information Implementors of this interface are brokers or simulation engines.
IHierarchyItemHandle Handle to an item of the algorithm hierarchy.
IInputSeriesStreamer Simulator of realtime series.
IManagedRunnable Parent interface of processors that run in another thread.
IOrder Trading order
IOrderPoint Interface to embed order information within a ISeries
IOrderReceiver Low-level interface that groups the methods to send orders to execution services
IOrderStatusListener Listener to order status.
IPosition Position information within an execution service for a specific IContract
IPositionListener Listener for position updates
IPositionPoint Interface to embed position information within a ISeries
IPositionProvider A service capable of delivering position information.
ISimulatedExecutionService The simulated execution service supplements a real execution service with a method to pass the input series used for the simulation.
ISimulatedExecutionServiceFactory Interface for the creation of disposable simulated execution services.
IStockDatabaseTradingAgentBindingManager Interface to manage algorithm binding, specific for strategies based on stocks
IStockDatabaseTradingManager Specialized trading manager that only deals with algorithm operating on IStockDatabase
ITrade Executed trade information
ITradePoint Interface to embed trade information within a ISeries
ITradeStatsPoint Time series point specific to convey statistics about a trade
ITradingAgent Trading algorithm instance Instances are created by implementors of ITradingAgentFactory, and are operated by means of a hierarchy of handles.
ITradingAgentBindingManager Interface to manage algorithm input bindings
ITradingAgentConfigurationManager Interface to manage trading algorithm configurations
ITradingAgentExecution This interface represents a single execution of a configured, bound, trading algorithm
ITradingAgentExecutionManager Interface to manage the execution of an algorithm All operations to create, execute, manage the execution of a trading algorithm can be performed from this interface.
ITradingAgentFactory Specialized ISeriesProcessorFactory that creates trading algorithm instances
ITradingAgentHierarchyContainer Container for trading algorithm hierarchy.
ITradingFactoryManager Interface to deal with ITradingAgentFactory instances.
ITradingHierarchyManager Manager of the algorithm hierarchy.
ITradingListener Listener to trade executions and price updates This interface is implemented by services willing to maintain positions during simulations.
ITradingManager Main interface to deal with creation, configuration, input binding and execution of trading algorithms
ITradingStatsProvider Provider of trading statistics

InputSeriesStreamer Simple synchronous input series streamer
MemoryTradingAgentHierarchyContainer Non-persistent hierarchy container
OrderBean Order bean

TradeBean Trade bean
TradePoint Trade series data-point
TradeStatsPoint Trade statistics series data-point
TradeStatsProcessor Processor that listens to trades and prices and generates a series of realtime trade statistics
TradingAgentBinding Algorithm configured and bound to its inputs
TradingAgentBindingHandle Handle to a TradingAgentBinding
TradingAgentConfiguration Trading algorithm completely configured
TradingAgentConfigurationHandle Handle to TradingAgentConfiguration
TradingAgentExecutionHandle Handle to ITradingAgentExecution
TradingAgentFactoryHandle Handle to ITradingAgentFactory
